===============================================================================
Depending on how you want to structure your application, you can use configs files to update:
  1. Global Settings
    ```
    # config/initializers/active_admin.rb
    ActiveAdmin.setup do
      config.css_classes = YAML.load_file(Rails.root.join("config/active_admin_bootstrap/css_classes.yml").to_s)
      config.components = YAML.load_file(Rails.root.join("config/active_admin_bootstrap/components.yml").to_s)
    end
    ```

  2. Namespace Settings
    ```
    # config/initializers/active_admin.rb
    ActiveAdmin.setup do
      config.namespace :site_1 do |site|
        config.css_classes = YAML.load_file(Rails.root.join("config/active_admin_bootstrap/site_1/css_classes.yml").to_s)
        config.components = YAML.load_file(Rails.root.join("config/active_admin_bootstrap/site_1/components.yml").to_s)
      end
    end
    ```

  3. Resource Settings
    ```
    # app/admin/users.rb
    ActiveAdmin.register User do
      config.css_classes = YAML.load_file(Rails.root.join("config/active_admin_bootstrap/admin/users/css_classes.yml").to_s)
      config.components = YAML.load_file(Rails.root.join("config/active_admin_bootstrap/admin/users/components.yml").to_s)
    end
    ```

  4. For guides, please visit https://github.com/CMDBrew/active_admin_bootstrap
===============================================================================
